The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 September is 295,989 (34,114.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 September, there were 376 new confirmed cases (43.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 September, there were 424 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (48 fewer cases).
